org.jetel.ctl

Annotation Type CTLEntryPoint


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface CTLEntryPoint
    Use this annotation for methods that should be recognized as CTL entry points by the CTL-to-Java compiler.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String name 
      boolean required 

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String deprecated 
      java.lang.String[] parameterNames 

    • Element Detail

      • required

        public abstract boolean required
        Returns:
        True when the method must be implemented in the CTL code (required by given transformation inerface)

      • name

        public abstract java.lang.String name
        Returns:
        Name of the corresponding CTL function

      • parameterNames

        public abstract java.lang.String[] parameterNames
        Returns:
        Parameter names - empty by default
        Default:
        {}

      • deprecated

        public abstract java.lang.String deprecated
        Returns:
        deprecation message to be logged as a warning if an optional deprecated method is implemented
        Default:
        ""
